TITLE: Creating a Memoized Selector with Reselect in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create a memoized selector using Reselect's createSelector function. This selector computes data efficiently by combining simple selectors and memoizing the result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/mattermost-developer-documentation/blob/master/site/content/contribute/more-info/webapp/redux/selectors.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export const getCurrentUser = createSelector(
    getCurrentUserId,
    (state) => state.entities.users.profiles,
    (currentUserId, profiles) => {
        if (!profiles.hasOwnProperty(currentUserId)) {
            // Current user not found
            return {};
        }

        return profiles[currentUserId];
    }
);
```

