TITLE: Batch Updating with Offset in PostgreSQL
DESCRIPTION: SQL query to update the channel_count column in the status table for a batch of users, using an offset to continue from where the previous batch left off.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/mattermost-developer-documentation/blob/master/site/content/contribute/more-info/server/schema-migration-guide.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
UPDATE status s SET channel_count=(SELECT count(*) FROM channelmembers cm WHERE cm.userid=s.userid) WHERE channel_count IS NOT NULL AND s.userid in (SELECT userid FROM status WHERE userid > <offset> ORDER BY userid ASC limit 10);
```

