TITLE: Updating Go Version on Jenkins Instances (Bash)
DESCRIPTION: This script updates the Golang distribution on Jenkins master and slave instances. It downloads the specified Go version, removes the existing installation, extracts the new version, updates the PATH, and installs standard libraries for Windows and macOS cross-compilation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mattermost/mattermost-developer-documentation/blob/master/site/content/internal/infrastructure/build.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
wget https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go{{< goversion >}}.linux-amd64.tar.gz
sudo su
rm -r /usr/local/go/
tar -C /usr/local -xzf go{{< goversion >}}.linux-amd64.tar.gz
export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin
env GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 go install std
env GOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go install std
```

